# Plans are part of the repo

**All plans must live in the project and be version-controlled.**

1. **Location:** Store every plan in the **`plans/`** directory at the project root (e.g. `plans/feature-name.md`, `plans/2025-03-refactor.md`). If a plan is created or discussed and would otherwise live only in chat or outside the repo, create or update a file under `plans/` so it is part of the repo.

2. **Commit and push:** Plans are normal repo content. When you commit (including **pushme** / **pushall**), include changes under `plans/` like any other file. Do not exclude the `plans/` directory from commits or pushes.

3. **Update plans.md:** Every new plan file must also get a row added to **`plans.md`** at the project root.
   - Format: `| [Friendly name](plans/file-name.md) | Short description | Not started | YYYY-MM-DD |`
   - Status options: **Complete**, **Not started**, **Unknown**
   - Date: today's date (when creating) or last date actioned

4. **Creating or saving a plan:** When writing or saving a plan, put it in `plans/` with a clear filename (e.g. `plans/auth-redesign.md`) and add a row to `plans.md`. If the user asks to "save this plan" or "add this to the repo", write the plan into a file under `plans/` and ensure it will be committed on the next push.

Summary: **Plans go in `plans/`. Each new plan gets a row in `plans.md`. They are committed and pushed with the rest of the repo.**
